JD - 1 :

Key Responsibilities:
• Oversee infrastructure planning, facility upgrades, maintenance, security, and housekeeping.
• Manage vendor relationships to ensure service quality and cost optimization.
• Lead office expansion or relocation projects including lease management, fit-outs, and statutory compliance.
• Implement sustainable and energy-efficient practices in facility operations.
• Develop and implement administrative policies, SOPs, and processes to ensure seamless daily operations.
• Optimize costs across travel, logistics, hospitality, utilities, and related functions.
• Oversee procurement, asset management, and inventory of office equipment and supplies.
• Ensure statutory, safety, and security compliance across all locations.
• Collaborate cross-functionally with Finance, IT, and HR teams.
• Provide infrastructure and administrative support for GTM initiatives, including event logistics and executive visits.
• Manage operational logistics for international leadership delegations and customer engagements under GTI.
• Support readiness for new teams and business units in India.
• Lead, mentor, and develop the admin and facilities team for high performance.
• Advise senior leadership on space strategy, infrastructure investments, and operational excellence.
• Communicate facility updates and policies across the organization.
• Partner with business and HR leaders to enhance employee experience and workplace culture.

Education & Work Experience:
• Bachelor’s degree required; Master’s preferred.
• Minimum 10 years in Administration / Facilities Management, including 3+ years in a leadership role.

Knowledge:
• Deep understanding of administrative operations and facility management principles.
• Knowledge of statutory and safety compliance requirements for multi-location operations.
• Familiarity with lease agreements, space planning, and vendor contracts.
• Awareness of sustainable facility practices and workplace technologies.

Skills:
• Strategic planning and execution for infrastructure projects.
• Strong vendor management and negotiation capabilities.
• Budgeting and cost optimization expertise.
• Excellent interpersonal, problem-solving, and communication skills.
• Leadership skills with proven ability to manage cross-functional teams.

Abilities:
• Ability to manage complex, multi-location operations effectively.
• Ability to align infrastructure strategies with business objectives.
• Ability to foster a high-performance team culture.
• Ability to influence stakeholders and drive change at a strategic level.

