• Manage procurement processes in line with organizational policies and budgets.
• Negotiate and maintain contracts with vendors, service providers, and suppliers.
• Ensure quality, cost efficiency, and transparency in all procurement processes.
• Manage the visitors/guests in the Noida office.

3. Travel and Event Logistics
• Organize and oversee domestic and international travel arrangements for employees & CEO, including bookings, reimbursements, and compliance with travel policies.
• Coordinate logistics for workshops, conferences, and meetings (venue, catering, accommodation, etc.).

4. Compliance and Record Management
• Maintain administrative MIS related to office operations.
• Support HR and Finance teams whenever required.
• Ensure confidentiality and security of organizational documents and data.

5. Infrastructure and Facility Management
• Oversee office space planning, safety protocols, and facility improvements.
• Liaise with building management and external agencies for utilities, housekeeping, and security services.

Qualifications and Experience
• Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration, Management, or related field (Master’s preferred).
• Minimum 5-8 years of experience in administration, operations, or facilities management;
experience in NGOs, think tanks, or research institutions preferred.
• Strong understanding of procurement, compliance, and organizational systems.
• Proven ability to manage teams, vendors, travel and multiple priorities effectively.
• Excellent communication, interpersonal, and problem-solving skills.
• Ability to do multitasking.
• Proficiency in MS Office Suite.

